ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Yes, I'd recommend it. It should be required!

I would say that it is an interesting introduction to romanticism and the writing of several central romantic poets. I would definitely recommend the course to someone who was interested in these topics.
Yes, I would recommend this course to a student interested in a general overview of Romantic poetry.
I would recommend the course without any reservations.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: While the course contributed neither to my research nor my knowledge of the profession, it aided me through the 'vale of soul-making.'

I have a better understanding of the chronology and main poets of the British Romantic movement, which -- while not my intended field of study -- has broadened my knowledge of English literature. Knowing some of the main critics of this period (particularly the Yale Romanticists) is also useful, as their criticism is highly influential across a variety of fields in literature.
